By Esther Egbe
Former Super Eagles striker, Victor Agali, is confident that the Super Eagles can pull a surprise at this year’s World Cup in Russia.
The gormer goaleador made this known on recently during  a chat with National Daily
The former Olympic Marsseile of France, Hansa Rostock and Scahlke 04 of Germany gangling  forward predicted a second round place for the Eagles which he said would continue the journey of making the knockout round with much determination.
The Super Eagles will take on Croatia in their first Group D game on Saturday
